Includes<pre><code>#include "queryosity/queryosity.h"

namespace qty = queryosity;
namespace multithread = qty::multithread;
namespace dataset = qty::dataset;
namespace column = qty::column;
namespace query = qty::query;
namespace systematic = qty::systematic;
using dataflow = qty::dataflow;
</code></pre> Create a dataflow<pre><code>dataflow df(mulithread::enable(/*(1)!*/));
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Requested number of (default: system maximum).</li> </ol> Keep datasetJust columnsOne-liner Read columns<pre><code>auto ds = df.load(dataset::input&lt;/*(1)!*/&gt;(/*(2)!*/));
auto x = ds.read(dataset::column&lt;/*(3)!*/&gt;("x"));
auto y = ds.read(dataset::column&lt;/*(4)!*/&gt;("y"));
</code></pre> <ol> <li><code>dataset::reader&lt;Self&gt;</code> implementation</li> <li><code>dataset::reader&lt;Self&gt;</code> constructor arguments</li> <li>\(x\) Data type</li> <li>\(y\) Data type</li> </ol> Read columns<pre><code>auto [x, y] = df.read(
  dataset::input&lt;/*(1)!*/&gt;(/*(2)!*/),
  dataset::column&lt;/*(3)!*/&gt;("x"),
  dataset::column&lt;/*(4)!*/&gt;("y")
  );
</code></pre> <ol> <li><code>dataset::reader&lt;Self&gt;</code> implementation</li> <li><code>dataset::reader&lt;Self&gt;</code> constructor arguments</li> <li>\(x\) Data type</li> <li>\(y\) Data type</li> </ol> Read columns<pre><code>auto [x, y] = df.read(
  dataset::input&lt;/*(1)!*/&gt;(/*(2)!*/),
  dataset::columns&lt;/*(3)!*/,/*(4)!*/&gt;("x", "y")
  );
</code></pre> <ol> <li><code>dataset::reader&lt;Self&gt;</code> implementation</li> <li><code>dataset::reader&lt;Self&gt;</code> constructor arguments</li> <li>\(x\) Data type</li> <li>\(y\) Data type</li> </ol> Define columns<pre><code>auto a = ds.define(column::constant&lt;/*(1)!*/&gt;(/*(2)!*/));
auto b = ds.define(column::expression(/*(3)!*/), /*(4)!*/);
auto c = ds.define(column::definition&lt;/*(5)!*/&gt;(/*(6)!*/), /*(7)!*/);
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Data type (optional)</li> <li>Data value</li> <li>Function/functor/lambda</li> <li>Input column argument(s)</li> <li><code>column::definition&lt;Ret(Args...)&gt;</code> implementation</li> <li><code>column::definition&lt;Ret(Args...)&gt;</code> constructor arguments</li> <li>Input column argument(s)</li> </ol> Apply selections<pre><code>auto cut = df.filter(/*(1)!*/);
auto cut_n_wgt = cut.weight(column::expression(/*(2)!*/), /*(3)!*/);
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Cut decision column</li> <li>Weight decision expression</li> <li>Input column argument(s)</li> </ol> Make queries<pre><code>auto q = df.make(query::plan&lt;/*(1)!*/&gt;(/*(2)!*/)).fill(/*(3)!*/).book(/*(4)!*/);
auto q_result = q.result();
</code></pre> <ol> <li><code>query::definition&lt;Out(Cols...)&gt;</code> implementation</li> <li><code>query::definition&lt;Out(Cols...)&gt;</code> constructor arguments</li> <li>Input column(s)</li> <li>Selection</li> </ol> AutomaticManual Apply systematic variations<pre><code>auto x = ds.vary(
  dataset::column("x_nom"),
  {"vary_x","x_var"}
  );

auto a = df.vary(
  column::constant(/*(1)!*/),
  {"vary_a",/*(2)!*/}
  );

auto b = df.vary(
  column::expression(/*(3)!*/),
  systematic::variation("vary_b", /*(4)!*/)
  )(/*(5)!*/);

auto c = df.vary(
  column::definition&lt;/*(6)!*/&gt;(/*(7)!*/),
  systematic::variation("vary_c", /*(8)!*/)
  )(/*(5)!*/);
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Nominal value</li> <li>Alternate value</li> <li>Nominal expression</li> <li>Alternate expression</li> <li>Input columns</li> <li><code>column::defintion&lt;Ret(Args...)&gt;</code> implementation</li> <li>Nominal constructor arguments</li> <li>Alternate constructor arguments</li> </ol> Apply systematic variations<pre><code>auto z = systematic::vary(
  systematic::nominal(/*(1)!*/), 
  systematic::variation("z_up", /*(2)!*/), 
  systematic::variation("z_dn", /*(3)!*/)
  );
</code></pre> <ol> <li>\(z\) column</li> <li>\(z + \Delta z\) column</li> <li>\(z - \Delta z\) column</li> </ol>

NominalVaried <pre><code>auto x = ds.read(dataset::column&lt;double&gt;("x_nom"));
</code></pre> <pre><code>auto x = ds.vary(dataset::column&lt;double&gt;("x_nom"), 
    {"vary_x", "x_var"}, 
    {"vary_xy", "x_var"}
    );
</code></pre> NominalVaried <pre><code>auto y = df.define(column::constant(1.0));
</code></pre> <pre><code>auto y = df.vary(column::constant(1.0), 
    {"vary_y", 2.0}, 
    {"vary_xy", 2.0}
    );
</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <ol> <li>The "transparent" variations <code>"vary_x", "vary_y"</code> are declared in <code>x, y</code> respectively.</li> <li>The "lockstep" variation <code>"vary_xy"</code> is declared in both <code>x</code> and <code>y</code> columns.</li> <li>Then they are propagated automatically to <code>z</code> (see below).</li> </ol>
